# Location Sharing Integration from WhatsApp & Google Maps

## System-wide Share Sheet Capture

This plan documents how to register **mNivesh Central** in the native Android and iOS system share sheets. When a user shares a location (link or text) from WhatsApp or Google Maps, the app captures the content, resolves shortened links, reverse-geocodes coordinates, and pre-populates the **Add Visit** screen.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **iOS Platform Complexity**
> iOS does not support simple background URL scheme interceptors for text shared from system sheets. It requires a dedicated **Share Extension** (App Extension target in Xcode) and an **App Group** (`group.com.company.appname`) to write shared data into a shared `UserDefaults` store before opening the main Flutter app. 
> Setting this up requires code signature capabilities in Apple Developer Console and modifying native Runner files in Xcode.

